        "materials_required": [
            "Power drill",
            "1/8 inch copper sheet",
            "Thick copper stem",
            "Pencil leads",
            "Super ball, baseball guts, tennis ball, rawhide (various stylus objects)",
            "Acid resist (optional, for etching)"
        ],
        "description": "This project details how to build a drawing machine using an old power drill and various stylus attachments. The machine creates abstract drawings by jigging the stylus across the paper.",
        "steps": [
            "Create an offset cam by using a hole saw on 1/8 inch copper sheet, and hard solder a thick copper stem off center.",
            "Clamp the power drill to a box with the offset cam in the chuck.",
            "Create a stylus by hot-gluing pencil leads onto various objects (e.g., super ball, baseball guts, tennis ball, rawhide).",
            "Build a fence on the face of the machine using scrap cardboard and duct tape to keep the stylus on the paper.",
            "Place paper within the fence.",
            "Plug in the drawing machine and observe the drawing process. Secure the machine to a table or allow it to move freely.",
            "Optionally, modify the machine to accommodate larger paper sizes or use a sharp, steel stylus on copper plate with acid resist for etching."
        ]
    }
